        <h1>State Board of Education Office and Breakroom Remodel</h1>

        <p>The State Board of Education office remodel project demonstrates Northway Construction's experience working with government and educational clients who require professional spaces that serve public-facing functions while maintaining budget accountability. This tenant improvement created additional office space and modern lounge areas to support the Board's mission of overseeing Utah's educational system.</p>

        <p>The scope involved reconfiguring existing space to maximize efficiency and functionality. We created additional private offices for staff requiring focused work environments, a new employee lounge designed for both relaxation and informal collaboration, and an updated break room with modern finishes and functional layout that serves daily staff needs.</p>

        <p>Government projects require understanding unique procurement processes, documentation standards, and schedule considerations. We navigated these requirements while maintaining the quality and efficiency that makes Northway a trusted partner for educational and public sector clients across Utah.</p>

        <h3>Project Highlights</h3>
        <ul style="line-height: 2; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <li>Tenant improvement for State Board of Education offices</li>
